  "utterances": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 14.879999,
      "text": "While everybody's been obsessing over ChatGPT and Kerzer, Google silently released 10 AI vibe coding tools, and the best part, they're completely free. First, we have Anti Gravity, their new AI code editor, which works just like Kerzer and lets you build fully functional apps and websites with just simple text prompts.",
      "confidence": 0.949247
    },
    {
      "start": 15.2,
      "end": 33.94,
      "text": "Then we got Google's AI Studio, which is perfect for spinning up quick AI powered apps in seconds. Next is Stitch, their AI design tool that turns your prompts and wireframes into literally full UI designs and front end code. After that, it's Opal, which is basically a combination of N8 and a Lovable, perfect for building no code AI apps powered by their models like Bayo three and Nano Banana.",
      "confidence": 0.937048
    },
    {
      "start": 34.18,
      "end": 48.373497,
      "text": "And finally, Joules, their AI coding agent that connects your GitHub that can build entire features, run tests, fix bugs, and manage your whole code base all on its own. And these are just five of the 12 tools that they launched so far. So if you guys want the full list for yourself, just comment Google and I'll send them to you directly.",
      "confidence": 0.96373206
    }
  ]
}